## API: addUserToGroup

### Description
Add one or multiple users to a Zalo group.

This API allows adding members into a specific group using their `userId`.  
Supports both single user and multiple users in one request.

---

### Method (zca-js)
api.addUserToGroup(memberId, groupId)

---

### Parameters

- memberId: string | string[]  
  → Zalo user ID or list of user IDs to be added into group

- groupId: string  
  → Target group ID

---

### Example

```ts
const groupId = "0000000000000000000";

// Add single member
const memberId = "0000000000000000001";

await api.addUserToGroup(memberId, groupId);

// Add multiple members
const memberIds = [
    "0000000000000000001",
    "0000000000000000002"
];

await api.addUserToGroup(memberIds, groupId);
```

---

### Return
{
  errorMembers: string[];
  error_data: Record<string, string[]>;
}

- errorMembers: string[]  
  → List of userIds that failed to be added

- error_data: object  
  → Detailed error information per user

---

## API: removeUserFromGroup

### Description
Xóa thành viên khỏi nhóm.

Remove one or more members from a Zalo group by their Zalo user id(s), scoped to a `groupId`.

---

### Method (zca-js)
api.removeUserFromGroup(memberId, groupId)

---

### Parameters

- memberId: string | string[]  
  → Zalo user ID or list of user IDs to remove from the group

- groupId: string  
  → Target group ID

---

### Return
`Promise<RemoveUserFromGroupResponse>`

TypeScript:

```ts
export type RemoveUserFromGroupResponse = {
  errorMembers: string[];
};
```

- `errorMembers`: list of user IDs for which removal failed (empty if all succeeded)

---

### Example

```ts
const groupId = "0000000000000000000";

// Remove one member
const memberId = "0000000000000000001";
api
  .removeUserFromGroup(memberId, groupId)
  .then(console.log)
  .catch(console.error);

// Remove several members
const memberIds = ["0000000000000000001", "0000000000000000002"];
api
  .removeUserFromGroup(memberIds, groupId)
  .then(console.log)
  .catch(console.error);
```

